<rss version="2.0"><channel><title>守护者</title><description>卫报全文RSS。获取更多全文RSS：https://feedx.net</description><link/> https://theguardian.com <item><title><![CDATA[Sick children’s health worsening as record numbers wait for NHS care in England]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/sep/17/sick-children-health-worsening-record-numbers-wait-for-nhs-care-in-england]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-17T17:52:15Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/4b1258c51ccc867e817a8a8ad43e602fff0f3005/0_201_5500_3300 /master/5500.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=c3d5d5f718f9b91337e868ab75929524&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;医生对女孩使用听诊器&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;随着创纪录的数字等待，患病儿童的健康问题越来越严重接受 NHS 护理的医生警告说，他们的 NHS 护理期限延长至 18 个月。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;英格兰等待儿科护理的 18 岁以下儿童人数已飙升至 423,500 人，创历史最高纪录。其中，23,396 人被迫等待一年多的时间才能获得预约。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;儿童和年轻人面临的延误现在非常普遍，以至于英国皇家医学院院长珍妮特·迪克森 (Jeanette Dickson) 博士表示，代表所有英国专业医生警告说，儿童是“NHS 等候名单危机中被遗忘的受害者”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;尽管 NHS，目前只有不到五分之三 (57%) 的儿童会在 18 周内就诊治疗目标说应该是92%。自 2021 年以来，等待名单上的人数增加了 52%。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“作为一名儿科医生，我亲眼目睹了长时间等待对儿童、他们的教育和整体福祉造成的破坏性影响，当然还有他们的家人，”&lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/profile/camilla-kingdon&quot;>;卡米拉·金登博士&lt;/a>;说道，皇家儿科和儿童健康学院 (RCPCH) 院长。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这些数据来自 RPCCH 的 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work- Areas/rtt-waiting-times/rtt-data-2023-24/&quot;>;对英格兰 NHS 最近发布的官方表现数据的分析&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;一些儿童的健康状况在日渐衰弱时不断恶化金登补充说，他们之所以被列入候补名单，是因为他们的疾病和年龄意味着他们需要快速接受治疗。 “许多治疗和干预措施必须在特定年龄或发育阶段进行。没有人愿意等待治疗，但儿童的护理往往时间紧迫。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;她举了一个例子，患有严重听力问题的儿童因被迫等待接受手术而受到伤害。人工耳蜗。 “让他们一岁左右对语言发展至关重要，”她说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“放射科的等候名单 - 因为您通常需要全身麻醉才能获得高质量的照片 - 意味着预科- 手术检查通常会延迟数月，而且手术可能会延迟 10 至 12 个月。因此，不是在 10 个月大时进行，而是在 18-20 个月大时进行。就言语和语言发展而言，这是一个巨大的差异。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;18 岁以下青少年还面临社区服务的长期延误，而不仅仅是医院护理，伦敦儿科顾问金登补充道。 “我有一个患有脑瘫的婴儿，他迫切需要一把特殊的职业治疗椅。这是一个八个月大的聪明小男孩，他完全有潜力取得很好的进步。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“因为他[在]邻近的一个行政区，治疗等待名单很长，所以延迟了六个月为了得到椅子。当你八个月大、想要坐下但需要额外支持时，延迟六个月绝对是一场灾难。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;卫生和社会保障部发言人表示：“减少等候名单是其中之一政府的五个优先事项，尽管受到罢工的干扰，我们实际上已经消除了 18 个月的等待，并立即采取行动减少漫长的等待。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我们正在改善对儿童、年轻人及其他们的支持他们提供了约 3 亿英镑，资助英格兰 75 个地方当局开展的为期三年的“家庭中心”和“生命起点”计划，并通过为有婴儿和各年龄段儿童的家庭提供服务和支持，已经在做出改变。 ”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;当学院发布一份关于儿童健康的新报告时，迪克森和金登表达了他们的担忧，该报告批评政府在制定关键卫生政策时忽视了年轻人的需求。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“所有医疗皇家大学领导对目前对儿童和青少年健康缺乏重视感到非常震惊。迪克森说：“就好像它们不存在一样。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;该报告强调了政府有争议的决定，即发布涵盖大量主要情况的战略，而不是针对每一项制定具体计划。尽管该战略将取代几个关键的儿童健康计划，但它主要关注成人健康。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;该学院还批评部长们放弃解决肥胖问题的计划，尽管学龄儿童超重危险的人数不断增加，以及推迟发布疫苗接种策略，尽管 14 种常规儿童疫苗接种中的 13 种接种率有所下降。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;该报告敦促里希·苏纳克 (Rishi Sunak) 设立一名内阁级儿童和青少年部长人民，为所有小学生提供免费校餐，加大疫苗接种力度，并扩大针对 18 岁以下青少年的心理健康服务，作为改善儿童健康和预防疾病的新举措的一部分。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 18 Sep 2023 02:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Tim Peake backs idea for solar farms in space as costs fall]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/sep/17/tim-peake-backs-idea-for-solar-farms-in-space-as-costs-fall]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-17T17:37:53Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/094696e483066197bf4ae9a7ce628f0f106cdad1/0_23_4940_2964 /master/4940.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=65cb293634b926cbc2a7b8ad9377478b&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;蒂姆·皮克穿着宇航员装备&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;蒂姆·皮克支持太空太阳能发电场的想法，称这个概念“变得绝对可行”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;宇航员 Maj Peake 表示，将重型货物送入轨道的成本不断下降，这意味着太阳能发电场等复杂结构很快就能发射到太空，并且提供强大电力的潜力。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;皮克是第一位访问国际空间站的英国欧洲航天局 (ESA) 宇航员，他说：“最终归结为硬数字。将数千吨硬件发射到近地轨道变得绝对可行。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;欧空局一直在探索天基太阳能发电厂的想法，并于今年委托进行了两项“概念研究”。它希望到 2025 年向欧盟提交一个商业案例。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Peake 表示，该机构已经计算出，当货物可以以 1,000 美元（807 英镑）的成本发射时，太空太阳能发电场在经济上是可行的。每公斤或更少。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“到目前为止，实际成本约为每公斤 2,700 美元，”他上周在一次能源技术峰会上表示，但他表示，两枚火箭是由 SpaceX 设计的。埃隆·马斯克（Elon Musk）可以解决这个问题。 “使用猎鹰重型火箭发射可以将其降低至约 1,500 美元，而所谓的星舰则将其降低一个数量级，达到每公斤约 300 美元。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;猎鹰重型火箭已经在运输卫星等货物进入太空，而星舰正在开发中。 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/apr/20/elon-musks-spacex-launches-test-flight-for-rocket-that-c​​ould-bring-people-to-mars &quot;>;四月份的一次无人试飞在升空后几分钟就爆炸了。&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;与以前的发射器不同，它们被编程为完好无损地返回地球并且可重复使用。这意味着每次发射无需建造全新的火箭，从而降低了总体成本。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;欧空局的 Solaris 计划旨在将太阳能电池板发射到太空，每个太阳能电池板都经过编程，可以通过机器人与其他电池板连接来建造太阳能发电场。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;虽然地球上的太阳能发电场无法在黑暗时期（例如夜间或天气恶劣时）发电，但太空电池板能够持续收集太阳能.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/science/2022/oct/09/beam-me-down-can -solar-power-from-space-help-solve-our-energy-needes&quot;>;请告诉我：来自太空的太阳能可以帮助解决我们的能源需求吗？ &lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;皮克说：“如果你可以在太空中建造太阳能发电厂，那么你就可以通过微波将能量传输到地面站。这意味着来自太空的清洁、无限的能源成为绝对可能。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;今年，英国大学和科技公司宣布将获得 430 万英镑的政府资金来开发&lt;a href=&quot;https ://www.theguardian.com/science/2022/oct/09/beam-me-down-can-solar-power-from-space-help-solve-our-energy-needs&quot;>;太空太阳能&lt; /a>;.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这是继 2020 年 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.gov.uk/government/news/uk-government-commissions-space-solar-power-stations-research&quot; >;英国政府委托的天基太阳能发电场报告&lt;/a>;表示，这些系统有潜力提供相当于大型发电站的能源，最多可满足该国电力需求的四分之一，并且及时成为一种无限且持续的零碳能源。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;不过，这种发展需要很多年的时间，而且不太可能帮助解决世界上任何紧迫的能源挑战。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 18 Sep 2023 01:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Top US and Chinese diplomats meet in Malta to smooth strained relations]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/17/china-united-states-jake-sullivan-wang-yi-meeting-malta]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-17T17:31:28Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/918e80c8cc974a1b3cb526c76254a6b3499d7548/0_175_8114_4872 /master/8114.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=c6afec170d3ec3dafdeb11a5578ace42&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;白宫国家安全顾问杰克·沙利文&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;美国和中国高级外交官在马耳他会面，讨论周末，世界上最大的两个经济体试图缓和紧张的关系，并为各自的总统扫清道路 – &lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/us-news/ joebiden&quot;>;乔·拜登&lt;/a>;和习近平 - 将于 11 月会面。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;据北京和华盛顿双方称，白宫国家安全顾问杰克·沙利文多次会见&lt;a href=&quot;x- gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/world/china&quot;>;中国外交部长王毅在马耳他，根据单独的声明，“坦诚、实质性”举行了建设性的”会谈。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/sep/17 /joe-biden-benjamin-netanyahu-talks-un-general- assembly-israel-us&quot;>;乔·拜登将在联合国会见本杰明·内塔尼亚胡，但关系尴尬&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;读出白宫周日表示，两位官员讨论了美中双边关系、全球和地区安全关切、俄罗斯对乌克兰的战争以及台湾海峡周围的问题。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;中国外交部称双方双方达成了保持高层交往并就亚太事务、海洋问题和外交政策进行双边磋商的协议。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;此次会晤是沙利文与王自五月四日以来的首次会面。几个月前，拜登命令美国战斗机击落一名中国人-在美国海岸操作气球&lt;/a>;。中国谴责这起事件“严重违反国际惯例”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;气球坠落事件后来导致拜登政府取消了美国国务卿安东尼·布林肯的北京之行。&lt;/p>; &lt;图 data-media-id=&quot;edd7990ad677babde2e00788d4811eee4f72a7b7&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/edd7990ad677babde2e00788d4811eee4f72a7b7/0_0_3404_2269/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;中国外交部长王毅。” width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;667&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;中国外交部长王毅。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;摄影：Tatan Syuflana/AP&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;由于美国对台湾的支持、围绕知识产权的贸易摩擦以及中国的军力建设（特别是在美国没有的高超音速导弹领域），中美关系紧张，这让拜登和习近平的会面受到质疑。亚太经济合作组织 (APEC) 会议将于 11 月在旧金山举行。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;上周，中国最高安全机构暗示，两国领导人之间的任何会晤都取决于美国“表现出足够的诚意”。拜登和习近平自 2022 年 11 月以来就没有见过面，当时他们在印度尼西亚巴厘岛举行的 G20 峰会上举行了三个半小时的会外会议。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在那次会面后，拜登表示，美国将“与中国“积极竞争”，同时坚称自己“&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/speeches-remarks/2022/11/14/remarks-by-president-biden-in-a -press-conference-bali-indonesia/&quot;>;不寻找冲突&lt;/a>;”。习近平表示，各国需要“探索正确的相处之道”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;但习近平没有出席上周末在印度新德里举行的 G20 峰会。拜登后来表示失望，但补充说他将“去见他”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;白宫周日提供的消息称，沙利文和王之间的会面是“持续努力保持开放”的一部分声明补充说，此次会谈是在巴厘岛会谈、沙利文和王毅五月份的会晤以及过去几个月美国对北京的外交访问的基础上进行的。布林肯、财政部长珍妮特·耶伦、气候特使约翰·克里和商务部长吉娜·雷蒙多。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;美国通知称，沙利文在会议期间“指出了台湾海峡和平与稳定的重要性”。根据中国外交部的声明，王毅警告美国，台湾是“中美关系第一条不可逾越的红线”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;路透社提供报道&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 18 Sep 2023 01:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[New York City daycare owner charged with murder after infant overdose death]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/sep/17/bronx-daycare-owner-murder-charge-opioid-overdose-infant]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-17T17:05:03Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/0a6161897343375d0a39d40ae40dbfbbde2155ab/0_200_6000_3600 /master/6000.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=963963664b569b50c324cffa2596d56f&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;一辆纽约警察巡洋舰。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;布朗克斯日托中心的一位业主因堕落冷漠罪名入狱周六，在&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/sep/16/child-daycare-death-new-york-city&quot;>;一-据官员称，一名 1 岁婴儿在她监护下因明显芬太尼中毒而死亡。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;另外三名儿童——一名八个月大的女孩和一对两岁的男孩——当局称，他似乎也因强效合成阿片类药物而患病。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/ us-news/2023/aug/25/new-york-nypd-police-motorcycle-picnic-cooler&quot;>;纽约一名骑摩托车的男子在警察向头部扔野餐冷却器后死亡&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;纽约市警察局 (NYPD) 确认日托中心老板为 Grei Mendez。调查人员还对门德斯的一名房客卡利斯托·阿塞韦多·布里托 (Carlisto Acevedo Brito) 进行了登记，罪名是与这起致命事件有关的堕落冷漠谋杀和毒品指控。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;警方在孩子们出现一天后逮捕了 36 岁的门德斯和 41 岁的布里托。可能被阿片类药物中毒的迹象。当局表示，1 岁的尼古拉斯·多米尼奇 (Nicholas Dominici) 在他就读的日托中心附近的一家医院死亡。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;紧急医疗技术人员在给日托中心的另外三名儿童服用阿片类药物中毒解毒剂纳洛酮 (Narcan) 后，救活了他们，&lt;a href=&quot; https://mail.google.com/mail/u/0/#inbox/FMfcgzGtxKMxtgrfXDDMDpWVpQnRMhJF?compose=DmwnWsLSDhFCWnvdjtRLDgGTQsQLtZzmfthbNrnbzMQjkJSPfkltrBHVDlHLSnLBlGJpSWTrpCFb&quot;>;报告&lt;/a>;说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;门德斯和布里托还面临袭击和儿童罪名&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;警方声称，他们在搜查 Divino Niño 日托中心时发现了一个公斤压机，通常用于包装毒品。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“这是一种常用的物品毒贩在包装大量毒品时，”&lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/us-news/new-york&quot;>;纽约警察局&lt;/a >; 据报道，侦探局长约瑟夫·肯尼 (Joseph Kenney) 在新闻发布会上表示。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这家托儿所是在一栋私人住宅内设立的，据报道最近通过了一次突击性的城市检查。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; >; 尼古拉斯的父母佐拉·多米尼奇 (Zoila Dominici) 和奥托尼尔·费利斯 (Otoniel Feliz) 表示，婴儿一周前刚刚开始在日托中心工作。 “他非常聪明，”多米尼奇 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cbsnews.com/newyork/news/nicholas-dominici-bronx-day-care-1-year-old-death-parents-speak/&quot; >;对哥伦比亚广播公司新闻说道&lt;/a>;。 “他会重复你对他说的一切。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“他有如此多的爱。每个认识他的人，包括我们所有的邻居，都对他表示赞赏。” 纽约市市长埃里克·亚当斯 (Eric Adams) 周六在接受记者采访时表示，尼古拉斯·多米尼奇 (Nicholas Dominici) 的死说明了持续的阿片类药物危机所造成的破坏。据美联社报道，亚当斯表示：“这场危机是真实存在的，对于家中拥有阿片类药物或芬太尼的个人来说，这确实是一个警钟。” “仅仅接触对于成年人来说就是致命的，对于儿童来说更是致命的。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;警方尚未透露他们认为孩子们是如何接触到毒品的。美联社称，尽管调查人员怀疑男孩死于芬太尼中毒，但该市法医仍在努力确定男孩的确切死因。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;纽约市卫生专员阿什温·瓦桑 (Ashwin Vasan) 博士告诉我们记者称，孩子们遇到了“可以……使接受者中毒的强力物质”，但当局“还不知道这起案件中发生了什么”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;纽约警察局警察局长爱德华·卡班 (Edward Caban) 也表示据报道说：“我们不知道这些婴儿究竟发生了什么。”本周末的逮捕行动并不是纽约市日托中心第一次涉及毒品犯罪。 2013 年，警方在布朗克斯区的 Fun World Childcare 发现了可卡因、羟考酮和枪支。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;美联社提供了报道&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt; div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 18 Sep 2023 01:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Guardian reporter among winners of climate journalism awards]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/sep/17/guardian-reporter-among-winners-of-climate-journalism-awards]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-17T16:30:04Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/22b693020f6cfea99b96277bab3f3d118920a21e/0_174_4716_2829 /master/4716.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=154e38f877b0bb71718571184684f121&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;一张大部分是橙色的图像，黑色的形状位于仙人掌仙人掌的中间 - 它有一个笔直的中臂，两只手臂在其旁边升起，略低，画面右上角有一轮灼热的太阳。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;全球新闻合作组织“Covering Climate Now”将于本周宣布其媒体奖评委们表示，当观众需要知道“地球着火”的方式和原因以及可以做什么时。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;CCN 2023 年年度气候记者是 &lt;a href=&quot;x-gu:/ /list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/profile/damiancarrington&quot;>;《卫报》的达米安·卡林顿&lt;/a>;，&lt;a href=&quot;https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/toireporter/author-Manka -Behl-479218595.cms&quot;>;《印度时报》的 Manka Behl&lt;/a>; 和 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.amywestervelt.com/&quot;>;Amy Westervelt&lt;/a>;，&lt;a href=&quot;https://crumbiklein.org/&quot;>;临界频率&lt;/a>;播客网络。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://naomiklein.org/&quot;>;Naomi Klein&lt;/a>;国际畅销书作家在&lt;a href=&quot;https://theintercept.com/2022/03/01/war-climate-crisis-putin-trump-oil-gas/&quot;>;评论&lt;/a>;中获胜&lt; a href=&quot;https://theintercept.com/2022/10/07/egypt-cop27-climate-prisoners-alaa/&quot;>;类别&lt;/a>;，而 &lt;a href=&quot;https://scroll.in/作者/21201&quot;>;印度非营利组织 Scroll.in 的 Ishan Kukreti&lt;/a>; 赢得了 &lt;a href=&quot;https://scroll.in/article/1014823/indias-ghost-plantations-in-which-millions -of-rupees-have-been-sunk&quot;>;长篇写作&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www .theguardian.com/artanddesign/gallery/2023/jun/08/coral-slime-burning-trees-and-hope-earth-photo-2023-shortlist-in-pictures&quot;>;珊瑚粘液、燃烧的树木——和希望：地球2023 年照片入围名单 - 图片&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;这些奖项是在纽约联合国气候周期间公布的，今年正值破纪录的热浪、野火和洪水造成的破坏生活在美国、欧洲及其他地区 - 并受到来自 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/28/crazy-off-the-charts-records-has- humanity- 的警告finally-broken-the-climate&quot;>;担心最坏情况可能尚未到来的专家。&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://coveringclimatenow.org/&quot;>;立即报道气候&lt; /a>; 是一项涉及约 600 家新闻媒体、覆盖超过 20 亿人口的全球合作项目，其媒体奖励计划于三年前启动，旨在传播气候新闻的卓越标准。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;今年的获奖者是从来自 29 个国家/地区的 1,100 多个参赛作品中的&lt;a href=&quot;https://coveringclimatenow.org/projects/the-2023-ccnow-journalism-awards/&quot;>;决赛入围者&lt;/a>;名单中选出的超过 100 名记者。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在年度记者的三项嘉奖中：&lt;/p>; &lt;ul>; &lt;li>; &lt;p>;《印度时报》的贝尔因“来自&lt;a href=&quot;https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/nagpur/urban-vs-rural-divide-crops-up-at-power-plant-hearing/articleshow/100603394.cms?from=mdr&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/nagpur/bhiwadi-most-polluted-in-world-delhi-no-1-among-capital-cities/articleshow的>;前线&lt;/a>; /90383765.cms&quot;>;世界上气候最重要的国家之一面临危机&lt;/a>;”以及她的&lt;a href=&quot;https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/for-covid-recovery- keep-climate-goals-in-mind/articleshow/79540015.cms&quot;>;与领导人的访谈&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>;&lt;/li>; &lt;/ul>; &lt;ul>; &lt;li>; &lt;p>;《卫报》的卡林顿因基于科学的报告而受到赞誉，该报告“解释了阻碍气候进步的因素是政治和企业权力，而不是缺乏绿色技术”，并因领导报告团队调查&lt;a href=&quot;https://www. theguardian.com/environment/ng-interactive/2022/may/11/fossil-fuel-carbon-bombs-climate-breakdown-oil-gas&quot;>;“碳炸弹&lt;/a>;”和&lt;a href=&quot;https:// /www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/mar/06/revealed-1000-super-emitting-macet-leaks-risk-triggering-climate-tipping-points&quot;>;超排放甲烷泄漏&lt;/a>;。&lt;/ p>;&lt;/li>; &lt;/ul>; &lt;ul>; &lt;li>; &lt;p>;Westervelt 被描述为 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2022/nov/03/climate -crisis-midterm-elections-states&quot;>;多产&lt;/a>;、多平台&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.thenation.com/article/environment/exxon- Plastic-pollution-climate-change/&quot;>;记者&lt; /a>; 临界频率，其工作揭示了&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2022/mar/07/climate-solutions-big-oil-ipcc-report&quot;>;化石燃料公司&lt; /a>; 继续误导公众和政策制定者。&lt;/p>;&lt;/li>; &lt;/ul>; &lt;p>;“地球上的每个新闻媒体都可以从曼卡、达米安和艾米带来的积极、有力的新闻报道中学习“关注气候故事”，《立即报道气候》执行董事马克·赫茨加德 (Mark Hertsgaard) 说道。 “这样的报道让公众获得了知识赋予的力量。”&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;f85d4fdff4436dec44fca4178d0301abd26ff4e3&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/ f85d4fdff4436dec44fca4178d0301abd26ff4e3/0_0_4256_2552/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;一位中年白人，笑容友善，灰色长发从脸上向后梳，留着灰色山羊胡，穿着红色长袖衬衫，站在外面的一扇门前。看起来像是一幅蓝色背景和霓虹绿树叶的壁画。” width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;卫报环境编辑达米安·卡林顿 (Damian Carrington)，2019 年。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;摄影：Jill Mead/卫报&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt; /figure>; &lt;p>;该奖项表彰了六位特别荣誉获得者，表彰其“严谨的调查报告、对气候不公正现象的令人大开眼界的揭露以及对气候解决方案急需的分析”：&lt;/p>; &lt;ul>; &lt;li>; &lt;p>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/frontline/documentary/the-power-of-big-oil/&quot;>;The Power of Big Oil&lt;/a>; – PBS Frontline 制作的三部分纪录片&lt;/p>;&lt;/li>; &lt;li>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.bloomberg.com/features/2022-carbon-offset-credits-mexico-forest-bp/#xj4y7vzkg&quot;>;BP为华尔街最喜欢的气候解决方案向墨西哥农村居民支付了“微薄的费用”&lt;/a>; - 彭博社&lt;/p>;&lt;/li>; &lt;li>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.propublica.org/article/ mia-mottley-barbados-imf-climate-change&quot;>;巴巴多斯抵制气候殖民主义，努力承受全球变暖的代价&lt;/a>; – ProPublica 和纽约时报杂志&lt;/p>;&lt;/li>; &lt;li>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B7VqnXxlfJ4&quot;>;索马里噩梦般的干旱内部&lt;/a>; - 副新闻&lt;/p>;&lt;/li>; &lt;li>; &lt;p>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.dw.com/en/on-the-green-fence/program-49760682&quot;>;在绿色栅栏上&lt;/a>;——德国之声&lt;/p>;&lt;/li>; &lt; li>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MJXpO0oZwpc&quot;>;气候案例&lt;/a>;——半岛电视台英语&lt;/p>;&lt;/li>; &lt;/ ul>; &lt;p>;“观众不仅需要知道地球正在着火，还需要知道为什么会发生这种情况以及可以采取哪些措施，”《哥伦比亚新​​闻评论》的编辑兼出版商、覆盖气候的主席凯尔·波普说现担任新闻奖评委会委员。 “今年的获奖者体现了热心公益新闻事业的最佳典范。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;其他获奖者包括&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.kcra.com/article/forecasting-our-future-increase-risk -dams-climate/41533309&quot;>;赫斯特电视台&lt;/a>;、澳大利亚广播公司、法新社和&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.latimes.com/newsletters/boiling-point&quot;>;洛杉矶《泰晤士报》&lt;/a>; 以及交通广播系统（首尔）等小型企业，该公司凭借&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1mHk5r_Lyy8&quot;>;首尔的反乌托邦&lt;/ a>;.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;两位新兴记者，&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/alexsdelagarza&quot;>;Alejandro de la Garza&lt;/a>; 和 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter. com/snktjain&quot;>;Sanket Jain&lt;/a>;，以及两名学生记者，&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/caminunderland&quot;>;Cameron Oglesby&lt;/a>; 和 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter .com/kate_selig&quot;>;凯特·塞利格&lt;/a>;因在气候节拍中的首次亮相而受到表彰。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 18 Sep 2023 00:52:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Bernie Sanders: workers should reap AI benefits in form of ‘lowering workweek’]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/sep/17/bernie-sanders-workers-should-reap-benefits-of-ai]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-17T16:42:49Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/112b0d175e383dd34886ccc953875774ce8de43e/0_104_3689_2215 /master/3689.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=5c7c7d22423f833d1a104f50f3214888&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;参议员伯尼·桑德斯在密歇根州底特律举行的集会上向美国汽车工人联合会 (UAW) 成员发表讲话周五。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;如果美国持续的人工智能和机器人热潮转化为&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/apr/07/ai-artificial-intelligence-west -weak-productivity-low-growth&quot;>;更多的工作做得更快&lt;/a>;，那么劳动者应该以更多的带薪休假的形式获得一些收益，自由派美国参议员伯尼·桑德斯周日表示。&lt;/a>; p>; &lt;p>;“我碰巧相信，作为一个国家，我们应该开始认真讨论......关于大幅减少每周工作时间，”桑德斯在 CNN 的国情咨文中说道。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;引用了育儿问题，大多数美国人普遍面临住房、医疗保健和财务压力&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.npr.org/sections/health-shots/2023/03/25/1164819944/live-free-and-die-the-他补充道：“我们的悲伤状态缩短了他们的预期寿命。”“在我看来，如果新技术能让我们成为一个更有生产力的社会，那么受益者应该&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“看到人们有更多的时间能够与孩子、家人在一起，能够做更多的事情……文化活动，接受更好的教育，这将是一件了不起的事情。因此，……确保人工智能[和]机器人技术造福我们所有人——而不仅仅是上层人士——的想法绝对是我们需要讨论的。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;桑德斯，一位独立党员，与在国情咨文主持人杰克·塔珀向国会民主党人询问美国汽车工人联合会寻求的每周四天工作制后，他发表了上述评论。该工会约 13,000 名工人在放弃前一天结束时到期的续签合同谈判后，于周五对美国三大汽车制造商——通用汽车、福特和克莱斯勒母公司 Stellantis 进行了罢工。&lt;/p >; &lt;p>;塔珀问桑德斯，&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/sep/15/bernie-sanders-uaw-auto-workers-strike-detroit-rally&quot;>;谁出现了周五在一次支持罢工的集会上，缩短工作周的概念是否可能只是美国汽车工人联合会在其他一些要求得到满足后会放弃的一种谈判策略。但桑德斯为这一要求的有效性进行了辩护，同时也抓住时机重申了对汽车制造商高管收取的花哨工资的批评。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;桑德斯 - 参议院健康、教育、劳工和养老金委员会主席– 暗示通用汽车、福特和 Stellantis 的首席执行官如何赚到比工人工资中位数高出数百倍的钱。根据 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.epi.org/blog/uaw-automakers-negotiations 的数据，2013 年至 2022 年间，他们的工资上涨了 40%，而工人的实际时薪自 2008 年以来下降了约五分之一。 /&quot;>;经济政策研究所&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;根据美国汽车工人联合会的说法，这种差异表明，在 2008-09 年金融危机之后，工人们从未因老板要求他们做出的牺牲而得到充分补偿，当时他们同意以救助汽车行业的名义进行大量削减。工会罢工成员的要求包括，除了每周 32 小时工作制外，工资增加 40%、更好的退休福利和工作保障。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;75% 的美国人支持罢工的汽车工人，根据盖洛普&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.thenation.com/article/politics/americans-side-with-striking-uaw/&quot;>;最近的一项民意调查&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;尽管如此，罢工的规模之大可能会扰乱整个美国经济，并最终可能意味着本已陷入困境的通勤者的汽车价格上涨。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;与此同时，美国汽车工人联合会主席肖恩·费恩 (Shawn Fain) 周日告诉 MSNBC 和 CBS工会与汽车制造商之间的谈判进展缓慢。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在桑德斯露面之前，美国前共和党副总统迈克·彭斯 (Mike Pence) 试图将汽车工人的损失归咎于乔·拜登 (JoeBiden) 的白宫。 dissatisfaction.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“All those hardworking auto workers are living in the same reality every other Americans live, and that is wages are not keeping up with inflation,” Pence said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;But Sanders contended that the car industry&#39;s top executives are solely to blame for the strike.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“American people are sick and tired, in my view, … of corporate greed, in which the very richest people are becoming richer,” Sanders said. “What you&#39;re seeing in the automobile industry, in my view, is what we&#39;re seeing all over this economy – greed on the top, suffering on the part of the working class, and people are tired of it.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“You people on top – you&#39;ve never had it so good. … So UAW is standing up against corporate greed. And I applaud them for what they&#39;re doing.”&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 18 Sep 2023 00:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Italian PM warns migration an issue for all of Europe on Lampedusa visit]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/17/italian-pm-warns-migration-an-issue-for-all-of-europe-on-lampedusa-visit]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-17T16:30:55Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/cd5720fb0ea9ca14764ea50964f718e15a12bb6e/181_0_2550_1530/master/2550.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=4061543cb11c451309ca9e19206f0b27&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Italian PM Giorgia Meloni, right, and Ursula von der Leyen, president of the European commission, visit Lampedusa on Sunday.&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Italy&#39;s prime minister has said that European countries must work together “to stop departures [from Africa]” and swiftly deport those turned down for asylum, who she said “threaten the future of Europe”, after thousands of people seeking refuge arrived on Lampedusa in the last week.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Giorgia Meloni toured the tiny Sicilian island, which for years has been the first port of call for people making the treacherous journey by sea from north Africa, on Sunday morning alongside Ursula von der Leyen, president of the European Commission.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The three-hour visit, which included a stop-off at an overcrowded reception centre and a site near the port that contains the remains of flimsy boats used by migrants, came after almost 8,500 people landed within three days last week – more than the island&#39;s population of 6,000.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The body of &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/16/newborn-baby-boat-rescue-operation-lampedusa-italy&quot;>;a baby who died shortly after being born onboard a boat carrying 40 passengers&lt;/a>; was placed in a white coffin and taken to the island&#39;s cemetery on Saturday morning. Last week, a five-month-old boy drowned during a rescue operation.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In recent days, there were chaotic scenes at the reception centre, which has the capacity to host only 400 people, with migrants sleeping on the rubbish-strewn street outside and others trying to escape over a fence.&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;77f2b03bee5aebcb1b6e4d0c3ea5bb77780965a1&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/77f2b03bee5aebcb1b6e4d0c3ea5bb77780965a1/0_167_6000_3602/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Migrants in Lampedusa&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;Migrants in Lampedusa before the arrival of Giorgia Meloni and Ursula von der Leyen.&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;Photograph: Roberto Salomone/The Guardian&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;But by the time Meloni and Von der Leyen arrived, the majority had been transferred off the island to centres in Sicily or mainland Italy and the area around the centre made to look almost pristine.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022/oct/22/far-right-leader-giorgia-meloni-sworn-in-as-italys-prime-minister&quot;>;Meloni, whose far-right government took power last October,&lt;/a>; said the influx threatened “the future of Europe” and that “serious solutions” were needed, such as cracking down on people smugglers, swiftly deporting illegal immigrants, and moving quickly to implement a deal signed this year with Tunisia.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“If anyone thinks that this crisis we are facing could be just resolved within Italian borders, it would be a very big mistake, because this problem involves everyone and needs to be tackled by everyone,” said Meloni. “I continue to say that we will never resolve it by talking only about redistribution [of migrants] – the only way to resolve it is to stop departures.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Von der Leyen promised the swift deportation of those who fail to be granted asylum and a crackdown on the “brutal business” of people smuggling. “We will decide who comes to the European Union, and under what circumstances. Not the smugglers,” she said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;She outlined a 10-point plan, including providing Italy with support in processing new arrivals while “exploring options to expand existing naval missions in the Mediterranean, or to work on new ones”. Von der Leyen also urged member states to make use of a mechanism enabling them to voluntarily take in migrants to help ease the burden on Italy.&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;cbbc48c0a73c97edc27f5aec07fb900158acac3a&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/cbbc48c0a73c97edc27f5aec07fb900158acac3a/0_276_6048_3628/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Ursula von der Leyen and Giorgia Meloni&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;Ursula von der Leyen, left, and Giorgia Meloni at a press conference during their visit.&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;Photograph: Anadolu Agency/Getty Images&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;However, people are continuing to arrive on the island. Most had set off from Tunisia, where in July Meloni and Von der Leyen signed a controversial £105m deal to stem irregular migration. No money has yet changed hands and there has been criticism that the numbers of migrants crossing from Tunisia to Italy has risen almost 70% in the months after the deal, a fact that experts have attributed to the fair weather.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Over 127,000 people – more than double the number over the same period last year – have landed on Italian soil so far in 2023.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“I&#39;m travelling to fulfil my dream, which is to go to England, finish my studies and become a doctor,” said Musa Adam, from Sudan, as he waited to be transferred off the island on Saturday night. He said he had tried to reach Europe by boat from Libya four times but was captured by the Libyan coastguard and imprisoned.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“We were beaten,” he said. “I saw friends die of disease and hunger.” He then crossed the desert to Tunisia, where “there are no jobs and no houses – we slept on the street … I have overcome so many challenges already, but I need to stay positive and keep going.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The latest crisis has reignited a debate over the division of responsibility among EU states and raised questions about the feasibility of deals with north African countries.&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;181aa8f1652d479aaa32437b3adc261c112d1725&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/181aa8f1652d479aaa32437b3adc261c112d1725/0_408_3072_1844/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Giorgia Meloni views small boats&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;Giorgia Meloni views small boats used by those arriving in Lampedusa.&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;Photograph: Filippo Attili/EPA&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;Lampedusa, which lies closer to Tunisia than Sicily, has been dealing with migration from north Africa for over 30 years. But patience on the island is wearing thin. Residents have protested over fears that it would turn into a “tent city”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“We hate to see people suffering and have always been there to pull bodies from the sea or provide food and clothing,” said Giorgia Pirotta. “But we can&#39;t live like this any more. These people deserve respect, and so do we.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Meloni, whose election pledge was to stop illegal immigration, is hoping the deal with Tunisia can provide a solution. The EU has insisted that the budget allocated to Tunisia would be paid out – it is currently refitting 17 vessels for the Tunisian authorities to use in search and rescue operations.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;However, a group of MEPs from the European parliament were refused entry to the country, raising fresh concerns about President Kais Saied&#39;s commitment to address questions of human rights abuses. He has previously declared that Tunisia would not be Europe&#39;s border guard.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The EU migration pact was driven by Meloni, but is backed by the rest of Europe, where migration is seen as a critical issue in elections, particularly those looming in Poland and the Netherlands.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A further £150m is available under the deal with Tunisia to help with economic reforms and develop industrial ties with Europe including green energy.&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 18 Sep 2023 00:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Balmain chief says at least 50 pieces for Paris fashion week have been stolen]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/17/balmain-chief-says-at-least-50-pieces-for-paris-fashion-week-have-been-stolen]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-17T15:54:10Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/34355812a7578fecba1bf2b43777790ed0033219/0_72_2999_1800/master/2999.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=9e2f5f412c3dfcfdd871f703b593055c&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Olivier Rousteing&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Balmain artistic director Olivier Rousteing has said robbers have made off with more than 50 pieces of the new collection that his Paris house intended to show at fashion week later this month.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Posting overnight on Sunday on Instagram, Rousteing said a group of people hijacked his delivery driver on the way from an airport to Balmain&#39;s Paris headquarters. He said they made off with the last pieces he had been expecting for the 27 September womenswear show – more than 50 items in all. He did not give a breakdown of the stolen items.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Our delivery was hijacked,” he wrote. “Thank God, the driver is safe.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“So many people worked so hard to make this collection. We are redoing everything, but this is so so disrespectful. We won&#39;t give up.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Rousteing did not specify which of Paris&#39;s two main international airports the delivery was coming from. He wrote that he had been waiting in his office on Saturday morning when “our driver called us and said that he was hijacked by a group of people”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“This is so unfair.我和我的团队非常努力，”他写道。 “我们将日以继夜地工作更多。 Our suppliers will work days and night as well.”&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 18 Sep 2023 00:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Trump says Republicans ‘speak very inarticulately’ about abortion]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/sep/17/trump-interview-democratic-principles-abortion-rights]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-17T15:15:56Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/b6fec06604e25e4c5f6e4b2da20846e5a5e1b890/0_364_5603_3364/master/5603.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=8e26405de20e98825105033361616f10&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Donald Trump speaks during the Pray Vote Stand Summit, Friday, in Washington. &lt;/div>;&lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/us-news/donaldtrump&quot;>;Donald Trump&lt;/a>; grappled with a wide range of contentious issues in an interview with NBC that generated criticism against the network, including his thoughts on democratic principles, abortion rights and ageing politicians.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;He also confirmed his interest in choosing Kristi Noem to be his vice-presidential running mate if he wins the Republican presidential nomination in 2024 as he seeks a second term in the White House.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In an interview on Sunday with Kristen Welker during her debut as host of NBC&#39;s Meet the Press, the former president advised members of his party to abandon their hardline stance of abortion bans with no exceptions.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;He said Republicans “&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/donald-trump/trump-bring-country-together-abortion-meet-the-press-rcna105311&quot;>;speak very inarticulately&lt;/a>;” about abortion and criticized those who push for abortion bans without exceptions in the cases of rape, incest and the health of the mother.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Other than certain parts of the country, you can&#39;t – you&#39;re not going to win on this issue,” said Trump, who faces more than 90 pending criminal charges across four separate indictments, including for subversion of the 2020 election which he lost to Joe Biden.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“But you will win on this issue when you come up with the right number of weeks.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;He predicted that both sides would ultimately come together on the issue. “And for the first time in 52 years, you&#39;ll have an issue that we can put behind us,” he said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Trump said he is “all for” a presidency competency test, but the 77-year-old expressed his opposition to age limits.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;He alluded to taking a mental competency test two or three years ago and boasted that he “aced it”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“I get everything right,” Trump said during the interview conducted at his Bedminster, New Jersey, golf retreat. “I&#39;m all for testing. I frankly think testing would be a good thing.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In 2020, it was revealed that some of the early questions in that test involved Trump identifying an elephant and counting backward from 100.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Asked if it is time for a new generation of US leadership, Trump said: “It&#39;s always time for a new generation.” But he qualified his answer: “Some of the greatest world leaders have been in their 80s.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Those remarks from Trump came after retiring Republican US senator Mitt Romney of Utah called for a “new generation of leaders”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Trump notably defended Biden, his Democratic rival, on his age. A poll last month from the Associated Press and Norc Center for Public Affairs showed 77% of Americans – including 69% of Democrats – think the 80-year-old Biden is too old to serve a second term.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“I don&#39;t think Biden&#39;s too old,” Trump said to Welker. “But I think he&#39;s incompetent, and that&#39;s a bigger problem. It&#39;s really a level of competency, not the age.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Two days before Trump attacked Biden&#39;s acuity, Trump told a summit in Washington that a “cognitively impaired” Biden would lead the US into “world war two”, which occurred between 1939 and 1945.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Meanwhile, Trump said he “liked the concept” of having a woman as his running mate if he wins the Republican nomination, adding that he had his eye on Noem, the South Dakota governor. “I think she&#39;s fantastic,” he said. “She&#39;s been a great governor. She gave me a very full-throated endorsement, a beautiful endorsement actually. Certainly she&#39;d be one of the people I&#39;d consider.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Noem recently confirmed that she was a candidate for the position. “Of course, I would consider it,” &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.foxnews.com/media/south-dakota-gov-kristi-noem-consider-trumps-vice-president-spot-asked&quot;>;she told Fox News&lt;/a>;. But that was before the governor was splashed across the tabloid press for allegedly having an affair with former Trump aide Corey Lewandowski since at least 2019.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-12509093/Kristin-Noem-Corey-Lewandowski-secret-affair.html&quot;>;The Daily Mail&#39;s&lt;/a>; reporting has not been denied, though Noem&#39;s spokesperson said it was “so predictable” that the South Dakota governor would be attacked soon after she endorsed Trump for the Republican nomination.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Trump was asked if he still believes democracy is the most effective form of government. “I do – but it has to be a democracy that&#39;s fair,” he said. “This democracy – I don&#39;t consider us to have much of a democracy right now.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;He went on to complain about the indictments against him, which also contain charges for allegedly mishandling classified documents and attempting to conceal hush money payments to adult film actor Stormy Daniels.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Those charges are separate from civil cases that include a $250m lawsuit by the New York attorney general about his business affairs as well as a defamation claim stemming from a rape accusation that a judge has deemed to be “substantially true”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;During the interview, Trump said he was not &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nbcnews.com/meet-the-press/meet-the-press/trump-doesnt-worry-going-jail-meet-the-press-rcna105312&quot;>;“consumed&lt;/a>;” with prospect of prison time.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“I don&#39;t even think about it,” Trump said. “I&#39;m built a little differently I guess, because I have had people come up to me and say, &#39;How do you do it, sir?你怎么做呢？&#39; I don&#39;t even think about it.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“I truly feel that, in the end, we&#39;re going to win.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Trump has maintained he would not pardon himself if he is re-elected, but he revealed to Welker that he had discussed pardoning himself in the dying days of his presidency – a sign that he and his legal team understood the legal peril he brought on to himself by challenging the election&#39;s results.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;He said his failed election challenges eventually prompted him to ignore advice from his attorneys “because I didn&#39;t respect them”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.mediaite.com/tv/sold-her-soul-boycottmeetthepress-trends-big-over-welkers-trump-interview/&quot;>;Sunday&#39;s interview earned NBC criticism&lt;/a>; from many commentators who questioned the wisdom of giving such a soapbox to Trump after his alleged criminal misdeeds from before, during and after his presidency.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;One question by Welker that some dismissed as a soft-ball sought to discuss the contents of a message that Trump left for Biden when he left the White House.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Earlier this year, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/media/2023/may/10/donald-trump-cnn-town-hall-media-analysis&quot;>;CNN was pilloried&lt;/a>; for giving Trump a town hall-style platform in New Hampshire that indirectly led to the dismissal of its programming architect, former morning TV producer and CNN chief Chris Licht.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;NBC has said the network has also invited Biden to sit down for an interview with Welker.&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 17 Sep 2023 23:52:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Women urged to come forward with Russell Brand concerns as charity cuts ties]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/sep/17/amnesty-international-urges-women-to-come-forward-with-russell-brand-concerns]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-17T13:12:52Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c9c9a70767922f9c2e43583517b8ab0563c747e8/0_307_4500_2700 /master/4500.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=9057299b1ae26832a387e5d225d96ca4&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;2006 年的拉塞尔·布兰德。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;国际特赦组织敦促女性挺身而出，如果她们有任何疑问在公布强奸、性侵犯和精神虐待指控后，人们对拉塞尔·布兰德 (Russell Brand) 在 2006 年和 2012 年参加该慈善机构的两次单口喜剧活动期间的行为表示担忧。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;支持弱势女性从毒瘾中康复的慈善机构表示，它将切断与布兰德的联系。特雷维妇女和儿童慈善机构表示，它已经终止了与布兰德及其慈善基金“保持自由基金会”的合作关系。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周六，《星期日泰晤士报》发表指控称布兰德&lt;a href=&quot;https:/ /www.thetimes.co.uk/article/russell-brand-rape- Sex-assault-abuse-allegations-investigation-v5hxdlmb6&quot;>;在对有关布兰德行为的指控进行了长达数年的调查后，对四名女性进行了性侵犯&lt;/a>;与 Channel 4 的 Dispatches 合作。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这些指控发生在 2006 年至 2013 年之间，当时布兰德的名气最盛，当时这位喜剧演员为 BBC 广播 2 台和第 4 频道工作，并主演好莱坞电影。&lt; /p>; &lt;p>;这位 48 岁的人最近将自己重塑为健康大师，正在进行全国单口喜剧巡演。未来几天，他将在温莎、伍尔弗汉普顿和普利茅斯演出，网上呼吁这些场馆取消演出。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;一家制作公司据称在布兰德为他们工作期间收到了针对布兰德的投诉，已还对布兰德在主持节目时的严重不当行为指控发起了“紧急”内部调查。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;一名研究人员声称，有报道称，布兰德在 2004 年和 2005 年参与《老大哥》衍生节目时的行为令人担忧”配合广播合作伙伴和外部机构索取信息的任何请求”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我们还鼓励任何认为自己在制作这些作品时受到布兰德行为影响的人与我们私下联系，”它补充道。 &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;国际特赦组织在一份声明中表示，它发现这些指控“令人震惊和痛苦”，并且与这位喜剧演员没有任何关系。布兰德于 2012 年和 2006 年参加了该慈善机构的秘密警察舞会活动。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;该慈善机构表示，虽然在活动发生时“没有人对他的行为提出投诉或担忧”，但“非常了解女性在提出性侵犯投诉时面临的障碍，并鼓励任何女性让我们知道她们当时经历的任何令人担忧的事情”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Trevi，这是总部位于英格兰西南部的公司表示，对这一消息“深感悲痛和不安”，并终止了与布兰德及其慈善机构的合作。品牌的“保持自由”基金会资助慈善机构，“通过从成瘾、心理健康问题中恢复过来，以及帮助他们的非营利组织”来支持人们。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;宣布决定切断与 Instagram 帐户的联系，特雷维说：“拉塞尔在听说我们多年来帮助一些令人难以置信的母亲戒毒后，于 2022 年认识了我们的慈善机构。他希望支持我们的事业并通过他的“保持自由”基金会筹集资金。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“今天的媒体披露很难处理，但我们的首要任务仍然是现在和将来所有妇女和女孩的安全和福祉。将来。我们已经结束了与拉塞尔·布兰德和保持自由基金会的合作关系。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;它补充道：“作为一个慈善机构，其价值观将女性的声音置于我们工作的核心，我们始终优先支持受暴力影响的女性周六公布的指控包括，布兰德在一名女学生 16 岁、他 31 岁时与一名女学生发生了关系。据报道，她说他在一段涉嫌情感虐待和控制的三个月关系中，她称她为“孩子”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;据《星期日泰晤士报》报道，另一名妇女声称 2012 年布兰德在洛杉矶的家中强奸了她，声明称，她当天在强奸危机中心接受了治疗。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在声明发表之前，布兰德在网上发布的视频声明中声称，他面临着“一连串极其恶劣和侵略性的攻击” ”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他继续说道：“这些指控与我在主流工作时、当我一直在报纸上、当我在电影中时有关，正如我所写的那样在我的书里，我非常非常性交。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“现在，在性交的那段时间里，我的关系绝对是两厢情愿的。 I was always transparent about that then, almost too transparent, and I am being transparent about it now as well.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“To see that transparency metastasised into something criminal, that I absolutely deny, makes me question is there another agenda at play.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Brand has been contacted for comment.&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 17 Sep 2023 22:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Libya floods: warlord using disaster response to exert control, say observers]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/17/ibya-floods-derna-warlord-khalifa-haftar-libyan-national-army]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-17T14:19:47Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/040eb8c728040bbbb8910058848b1459c98de60b/0_11_3543_2126 /master/3543.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=00a80bd78cef3ecb10b72d253b743d6a&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;2023 年 9 月 17 日，搜救行动小组在利比亚德尔纳继续开展工作。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;在利比亚沿海城市德尔纳，当搜救队继续寻找被困在房屋泥浆和瓦砾下的尸体时，观察人士称，军阀哈利法·哈夫塔尔和他的儿子们正在使用&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian .com/world/2023/sep/16/Second-Humanarian-crisis-feared-in-wake-of-libya-floods-as-hopes-of-finding-survivors-fade&quot;>;灾难响应&lt;/a>;一种施加控制的方式，而不是确保重要的人道主义救济到达平民手中。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/global- development/2023/sep/16/libyan-reporters-floods-journalists-storm&quot;>;“城镇被夷为平地”：利比亚记者讲述洪水造成的“可怕、痛苦”&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt; p>;据利比亚红新月会称，上周的一场强风暴导致两座水坝决堤，造成至少 11,300 人死亡、10,000 多人失踪。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;由此引发的洪水完全摧毁了德尔纳的近 900 座建筑物据位于西北部城市的黎波里的该国民族团结政府称。报告补充说，超过 200 座建筑物部分受损，近 400 座建筑物完全淹没在泥浆中，这意味着德尔纳四分之一的建筑物受到洪水影响。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;绝望的救援工作仍在继续，试图找到任何剩余的幸存者&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/14/libya-floods-appeals-for-body-bags-disease-fears-northeastern-flooding&quot;>;尸体继续被冲上海岸线&lt;/a>;。现场的急救人员经常在利比亚国民军武装分子的包围下工作，利比亚国民军是一个忠于哈夫塔尔的庞大军事联盟，观察人士称，他们正在努力严格控制抵达这座遭受危机的城市的重要援助。&lt;/p >; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;5d307f5b86ca61f66cab3e07d8aa450abf2f8ca3&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/5d307f5b86ca61f66cab3e07d8aa450abf2f8ca3/0_0_4376_2626/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;德尔纳废墟的鸟瞰图，利比亚，2023 年 9 月 17 日。” width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;2023 年 9 月 17 日利比亚德尔纳遭受破坏的鸟瞰图。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：Halil Fidan/Anadolu Agency/Getty Images&lt; /span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;受洪水影响最严重的德尔纳市中心的公共通道已被关闭，该城市已被正式宣布为灾区。德尔纳的公民在没有电力、安全饮用水或食物的情况下艰难生存。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com /world/2023/sep/15/libya-floods-derna-relatives-mourn&quot;>;“洪水在我眼前带走了我的儿子”：痛苦的利比亚人哀悼失去的亲人&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/上周晚些时候，位于东部的利比亚议会主席奥萨马·哈马德表示，当局正在考虑封锁整个城市，因为担心水传播疾病的传播，该城市曾经居住着 10 万人。&lt;/大西洋理事会利比亚问题分析师埃马德丁·巴迪表示：“从本质上讲，军事存在正在制造瓶颈，而不是有利于提供救援。” “救援工作的主要推动力不是由军方领导层推动的，军方领导层在逃避责任和指责受害者的同时表现出控制欲，从而获得既得利益，而是由志愿者、医疗队、红新月会、童子军和外国搜救组织推动。自 2014 年以来，哈夫塔尔带头单方面控制利比亚东部大部分地区的军事行动，周五访问了德尔纳。他赞扬了急救人员以及 LNA 成员的行动，LNA 是一个由年老的前中央情报局人员和美国公民监督的民兵联盟，批评者指责他们在他控制下的地区运行，就像军事独裁者一样。&lt;/p>; &lt;巴迪说：“在公共关系方面，他们利用现有的宣传渠道来表现出控制力，同时成为管理危机救援的主要界面和城市的守护者。” “但是，这又在各处造成了瓶颈。哈夫塔尔的来访是这个问题的一个缩影，一切都因为公关噱头而被冻结了一个小时。”&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;d216f25ee042fed201761264bdd58381d33deb67&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim. co.uk/d216f25ee042fed201761264bdd58381d33deb67/0_23_3000_1800/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;哈利法·哈夫塔尔（右）在班加西会见埃及武装部队参谋长奥萨马·阿斯卡中将。&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;哈利法·哈夫塔尔（右）于 2023 年 9 月 12 日在班加西会见了埃及武装部队参谋长奥萨马·阿斯卡中将。阿斯卡率领军队抵达据埃及国防部称，代表团和紧急救灾援助。 &lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：埃及国防部/法新社/盖蒂图片社&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;哈夫塔尔的儿子们，每个人都控制着自己广泛的金融利益网络，有时还有军事利益利比亚东部地区的紧急救援队通过寻求进一步对救灾工作进行控制来应对德尔纳的人道主义危机。德尔纳发生灾难的同一天，哈利法·哈夫塔尔的长子埃尔塞迪克 (Elseddik) 宣布有兴趣在拖延已久的选举中竞选利比亚总统。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;观察人士称，32 岁的萨达姆·哈夫塔尔经常被看到尽管他的兄弟们做出了努力，但作为可能的继承人，他很快利用自己作为利比亚救灾委员会主席的角色，使自己的国际地位合法化，同时严格控制援助。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;萨达姆·哈夫塔尔领导塔里克·本·扎耶德旅，隶属于 LNA 的民兵组织，&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.amnesty.org/en/latest/news/2022/12/libya-hold-commanders-of-tariq-ben-zeyad-武装团体对恐怖目录负责/&quot;>;最近被国际特赦组织指控“造成一系列恐怖事件，包括非法杀戮、酷刑和其他虐待、强迫失踪、强奸和其他性暴力和强迫流离失所——无需担心后果”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;利比亚问题专家、皇家联合军种研究所副研究员贾勒尔·哈查维 (Jalel Harchaoui) 指出，萨达姆·哈夫塔尔试图展现对国际援助队伍的控制力。抵达德尔纳，以及这如何减缓了危机时期至关重要的灾难响应：“一切都集中在哈夫塔尔家族手中。我希望我能告诉你，利比亚东部还有其他权力中心，但没有这样的事情。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在过去十年的大部分时间里，利比亚一直保持着激烈的局势 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www .theguardian.com/world/2023/jul/04/fears-for-libyan-oil-product-amid-military-action-threats&quot;>;东部和西部派别之间存在着各自的军事利益，在北约部队进行军事干预以支持反对前独裁者穆阿迈尔·卡扎菲的起义之后。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Harchaoui 表示，哈夫塔尔家族对应对工作的控制，特别是萨达姆·哈夫塔尔的突出作用，使任何国内或国际组织都没有希望。对德尔纳事件的国际调查可以充分审查他们作为负责官员以及任何其他责任人的角色。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;利比亚总检察长 al-Sediq al-Sour 承诺 &lt;a href =&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/16/Second-Humanarian-crisis-feared-in-wake-of-libya-floods-as-hopes-of-finding-survivors-fade&quot; >;调查德尔纳两座水坝的倒塌&lt;/a>;，并分配数百万美元的资金用于维护这些建于 20 世纪 70 年代的建筑。在承诺调查德尔纳地方当局和前任政府的同时，苏尔还会见了萨达姆·哈夫塔尔。当地电视台报道称，德尔纳市长周六已被停职，等待调查。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“萨达姆将自己定位为老大。你需要亲自接触受害者和这座城市，而要做到这一点，他们取决于他的善意，”哈沙维说。 “事情慢慢地走向一个结论，那就是只能责怪中层官员。 A large part of the conclusion is excluded from the start, it&#39;s not an open investigation.”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 17 Sep 2023 22:22:01 +0800</pubDate></item></channel></rss>